      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALWAYS A RAINBOW (9) lightly raced filly who stretches out to this trip for the first time. Sat on the good tempo from the wide draw with a gritty second over 1400m at Tamworth. Cross-over nose band goes on from the low draw and should prove too strong for these. SHARK PARK (7) Ocean Park mare who comes up from Victoria and now in the Marcus Wilson yard. Proven at this trip and kept up to the mark with a 1000m trial placing. Has a host of gear changes and maps to stalk the speed. Top-three player. RIGHTEOUS BROTHER (2) drifted back early on the quick backup with a plugging fourth over 1320m at Lismore. Stretches past 1400m for the first time and worth thought. DUAL MASTERY (4) better effort at his third career start with a plugging fourth over 1400m at Gatton. Expected to get the trip and goes into the exotics.",
